# iOS 26 Liquid Glass — Web Design Rules

All UI should emulate Apple's iOS 26 Liquid Glass aesthetic. Every component, layout, and interaction must feel like layers of luminous, tinted glass floating over content.

## Material & Transparency

- Use `backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(180%)` on glass surfaces.
- Layer a semi-transparent background: `rgba(255,255,255,0.25)` (light) / `rgba(40,40,40,0.35)` (dark).
- Add a subtle `border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3)` for the glass edge highlight.
- Tint glass panels with the underlying content's dominant color using low-opacity overlays.

## Shape & Layout

- Use large border-radius values (`20px`–`28px`) for cards and containers; pill shapes (`999px`) for buttons and tabs.
- Float chrome elements (navbars, tab bars, FABs) above content with `box-shadow` and slight vertical offset — never anchor flush to edges.
- Prefer generous padding and whitespace; the glass needs room to breathe.

## Color Palette

Default to Apple's system-style palette, adaptive to light/dark:

| Role | Light | Dark |
|------|-------|------|
| Glass fill | `rgba(255,255,255,0.25)` | `rgba(40,40,40,0.35)` |
| Glass border | `rgba(255,255,255,0.35)` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.12)` |
| Primary accent | `#007AFF` | `#0A84FF` |
| Secondary accent | `#5856D6` | `#5E5CE6` |
| Destructive | `#FF3B30` | `#FF453A` |
| Label primary | `rgba(0,0,0,0.85)` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.92)` |
| Label secondary | `rgba(0,0,0,0.50)` | `rgba(255,255,255,0.55)` |

## Shadows & Depth

- Soft, layered shadows: `box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.08), 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.04)`.
- Elevated glass gets stronger shadow; recessed glass gets lighter.
- Never use harsh, solid drop shadows.

## Icons & Typography

- Use filled, solid icons (SF Symbols style) — not outlined strokes.
- Font stack: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'SF Pro Display', 'SF Pro Text', system-ui, sans-serif`.
- Bold weight for titles, regular/medium for body. Ensure strong contrast on glass.

## Motion & Interaction

- Use spring-based CSS transitions: `transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)`.
- Interactive elements should scale subtly on press: `transform: scale(0.97)`.
- Page transitions should slide with depth — layers translate on Z-axis or scale/fade.
- Hover states: brighten the glass fill slightly and intensify the border highlight.

## Example: Glass Card Component

```css
.glass-card {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
  backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(180%);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(40px) saturate(180%);
  border-radius: 24px;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  padding: 20px;
  transition: transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
}
.glass-card:hover {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.32);
  border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
}
.glass-card:active {
  transform: scale(0.97);
}
```
